public interface Value
A Value is the most general kind of object in the Wikibase datamodel. It can represent anything that can be the value of a user-defined property or of a system property that is not represented to the user (e.g., the datatype or list of aliases might be represented as a value, even though there is no user property with values of this type).

Markus Kroetzsch
